e war in Afghanistan, and the detainment and torture of Abdullah Almalki in Syria, Bell demonstrates that security measures are not simply eroding civil liberties, they are also fundamentally reshaping ideas and practices of freedom. This trenchant examination of Canada's "War on Terror" exposes how the logic and practices of security are increasingly coming to define our rights and freedoms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil rightsxCanada. 0aCivil rightszCanada. 0aDroits de l'hommexCanada. 0aNational securityxCanada. 0aNational securityzCanada. 0aSécurité nationalexCanada. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxGovernment policyxCanada. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxGovernment policyzCanada. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxPolitical aspectsxCanada. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxPolitical aspectszCanada. 0aTerrorismexPréventionxAspect politiquexCanada. 0aTerrorismexPréventionxPolitique gouvernementalexCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481827840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774818278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774818278/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles